Freddie gh-pages browser-learning architecture: src/learn/gm-learn.js is environment-aware. Node path imports gm-plugkit wasm wrapper (createPlugkit) in-process. Browser path (thebird/gh-pages, where node:module is absent) detects globalThis.__GM_DISPATCH__(verb,body)->json|Promise<json> set by the host and routes memorize-fire/recall/auto-recall/memorize-prune through the host's already-loaded in-page plugkit.wasm; probes lazily each call so a 149MB cold-loading wasm is picked up once ready; degrades to no-op (never throws) when absent. Namespace in browser comes from globalThis.__GM_NAMESPACE__ (string or fn) else default. thebird wires this in docs/freddie-host.js right after window.__debug.gm: sets __GM_DISPATCH__ (verbs pass straight through dispatch_verb, auto-recall falls back to recall on older wasm, libsqlPersist.schedule() after writes) and __GM_NAMESPACE__ from host.fs.instanceId (instance-<id>). Witnessed live: memorize-fire ok key=mem-... embedded:true + recall hit through the bridge, namespace=instance-i1. Also fixed a BigInt crash on gh-pages: wasm i64 ptr/len args arrive as BigInt and new Uint8Array(buf,bigint,len) throws Cannot convert a BigInt value to a number; coerced to Number at freddie-host.js dispatch alloc ptrs, makeGmEnvImports readStr/readBytes (n() helper), packResult, rawCallHook, plus a sanitizeBigInt on dispatch return so tool results JSON.stringify cleanly. NOTE the thebird per-instance SW claim persists the wasm env-imports closure across reloads, confounding hot edits in the dev harness (a fresh gh-pages CI deploy reloads cleanly). thebird memory-browser: docs/apps.js gm app recall panel renders prunable .gm-recall-hit cards (memorize-prune) + NAMESPACES includes activeInstanceNs; CSS in anentrypoint-design theme.css .gm-recall-*. freddie-chat.js shows a [recalled N memories] chip when auto-recall injects context.